{{Infobox MP | name = Molana Qamar ud Din | honorific-suffix = |image = | office =Member of the [[National Assembly of Pakistan]] | term_start = 1 June 2013 |term_end = 31 May 2018 |constituency = [[Constituency NA-269|NA-269 (Khuzdar)]] |nationality = Pakistani |party = [[Jamiat Ulema-e-Islam (F)]] }}
'''Molana Qamar ud Din''' ({{Lang-ur|{{Nastaliq|مولانا قمرالدین}}}}) is a Pakistani politician who had been a member of the [[National Assembly of Pakistan]], from June 2013 to May 2018.
==Political career== He ran for the seat of the [[National Assembly of Pakistan]] as a candidate of [[Muttahida Majlis-e-Amal]] (MMA) from [[Constituency NA-269|Constituency NA-269 (Khuzdar)]] in [[Pakistani general election, 2008]] but was unsuccessful. He received 15,938 votes and lost the seat to [[Mohammad Usman (politician)|Muhammad Usman]].<ref>{{cite web|title=2008 election result|url=https://www.ecp.gov.pk/Documents/General%20Elections%202008/Report,%20General%20Election%202008,%20Vol-II.pdf|publisher=ECP|accessdate=12 May 2018|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180105060230/https://ecp.gov.pk/Documents/General%20Elections%202008/Report,%20General%20Election%202008,%20Vol-II.pdf|archivedate=5 January 2018|df=}}</ref>
He was elected to the [[National Assembly of Pakistan]] as a candidate of [[Jamiat Ulema-e-Islam (F)]] (JUI-F) from Constituency NA-269 (Khuzdar) in [[Pakistani general election, 2013]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Plea against re-polling in NA-269 rejected|url=https://www.dawn.com/news/1011963|accessdate=6 March 2017|work=DAWN.COM|date=18 May 2013|language=en|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170307123733/https://www.dawn.com/news/1011963|archivedate=7 March 2017|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=JUI-F names candidates for 14 NA seats|url=https://www.dawn.com/news/797739/newspaper/column|accessdate=6 March 2017|work=DAWN.COM|date=25 March 2013|language=en|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170307123358/https://www.dawn.com/news/797739/newspaper/column|archivedate=7 March 2017|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=PML-N takes lead as PTI, PPP trail|url=https://www.thenews.com.pk/archive/print/630410-pml-n-takes-lead-as-pti,-ppp-trail|accessdate=6 March 2017|work=www.thenews.com.pk|language=en|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170305192357/https://www.thenews.com.pk/archive/print/630410-pml-n-takes-lead-as-pti,-ppp-trail|archivedate=5 March 2017|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=JUI finalises names of candidates|url=https://www.dawn.com/news/277280|accessdate=6 March 2017|work=DAWN.COM|date=24 November 2007|language=en|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170307123530/https://www.dawn.com/news/277280|archivedate=7 March 2017|df=}}</ref> He received 26,028 votes and defeated Mir Abdul Rauf Mengal, a candidate of the [[Balochistan National Party (Mengal)|Balochistan National Party]] (BNP).<ref>{{cite web|title=2013 election result|url=https://ecp.gov.pk/Documents/General%20Elections%202013%20report/Election%20Report%202013%20Volume-II.pdf|publisher=ECP|accessdate=12 May 2018|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180201140612/https://ecp.gov.pk/Documents/General%20Elections%202013%20report/Election%20Report%202013%20Volume-II.pdf|archivedate=1 February 2018|df=}}</ref>
