'''Pawar''' (also spelled as Puar, Puwar, Punwar, Parmar, Panwar, Powar) is an Indian surname. It is found among the [[Maratha]] clans that claim [[Rajput]] origin (see [[Parmar]]).<ref name="AiyappanRatnam1956">{{cite book | author1=A. Aiyappan | author2=L. K. Bala Ratnam | title=Society in India | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=GNcEAAAAMAAJ | accessdate=21 December 2012 | year=1956 | publisher=Social Sciences Association | page = 41}}</ref> It is also found among [[Punjabi people|Punjabis]].<ref name="Singh1996">{{cite book |author=K. S. Singh |title=Communities, Segments, Synonyms, Surnames and Titles |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=bfAMAQAAMAAJ |year=1996 |publisher=Anthropological Survey of India |isbn=978-0-19-563357-3}}</ref> Panwar is also a clan among [[Chhetri]] ([[Khas Rajput]]) clan of Nepal.<ref name="SinghUP2005">{{cite book|title=People of India: Uttar Pradesh (3 pts.)|author1=Singh, K.S.|author2=Anthropological Survey of India|date=2005|publisher=Anthropological Survey of India|isbn=9788173041143|url=https://books.google.com.np/books?id=6QVuAAAAMAAJ|accessdate=2017-06-11|quote=The Chhetri clans (thar) include Adhikari, Bania, Basnet, Bhandari, Bist, Bohra, Burathoki, Charti, Karki, Khanka, Khatri, Kanwar, Manghi, Mahat, Panwar, Rana, Rawat, Roka, Thapa, etc.}}</ref> Sardar [[Bhakti Thapa]] a war commander at [[Anglo-Nepalese war]], belonged to the Punwar Thapa clan.<ref>https://thehimalayantimes.com/kathmandu/plea-to-declare-bhakti-thapa-a-martyr/</ref>
People with this surname include: * [[Puar Rajputs|Puar Maratha Rajputs]] ** [[Hemendra Singh Rao Pawar]], (Present Maharaja of [[Dhar State]]) ** [[Tukojirao III|Tukoji Rao III Puar]], (Maharaja of [[Dewas Senior]]) ** [[Shahoji II|Vikramsinh Rao I Puar (Shahaji II Bhonsle)]], (The Maharaja of [[Dewas Senior]] who also became The Maharaja of [[Kolhapur State|Kolhapur]], after being adopted as [[Chhatrapati]] to the Gadi of [[Kolhapur]]) ** [[Krishnajirao III|Krishnaji Rao III Puar]], (Maharaja of [[Dewas Senior]] and Indian Politician) ** [[Tukoji Rao Pawar|Tukoji Rao IV Puar]], (Maharaja of [[Dewas Senior]] and Indian politician from Madhya Pradesh, belonging to the Bharatiya Janata Party) ** [[Vikram Singh Rao II Puar]] (Present Maharaja of [[Dewas Senior]]) * [[Lalita Pawar]] (1916-1998), Indian actress * [[Narayan Rao Pawar]] (1925-2010), Indian independence activist and member of Arya Samaj who plotted to kill the last Nizam of Hyderabad * [[Sharad Pawar]] (born 1940), Indian politician * [[Urmila Pawar]] (born 1945), Indian Marathi-language writer * [[Ajit Pawar]] (born 1959), Indian politician; deputy chief minister of Maharashtra and nephew of Sharad Pawar * [[Pradnya Daya Pawar]] (born 1966), Indian Marathi-language poet * [[Rajesh Pawar]] (born 1979), Indian cricketer * [[Ameya Pawar]] (born 1980), American politician and City of Chicago Alderman * [[Kuldeep Pawar]], Indian actor in the Marathi language film industry * [[Anand Pawar]], Indian badminton player * [[Anjali Pawar]], Indian social worker * [[Rajendra Singh Pawar]], Indian businessman, chairman of NIIT * [[Uttamsingh Pawar]], Indian politician
